===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the oracle bone script, it was a {{liushu|p|nocap=1}} of an arrow with a flat arrowhead (cf. {{zh-l|*зҹў}}, an arrow) вҖ“ original character of {{och-l|йҢҚ|arrow with a flat arrowhead}}.

In the bronze script, a dot was added to the centre, which later became a short line. The bottom of the glyph eventually corrupted into {{zh-l|*е»ҫ}} or {{zh-l|*дёҢ}}. On the basis of the latter shape, ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' erroneously interprets the character as a {{Han compound|з”¶|дёҢ|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=pedestal|nocap=1}}.

